Class Enaction

java.lang.Object
  ernest.Enaction
All Implemented Interfaces:
IEnaction
public class Enaction
extends java.lang.Object
implements IEnaction

A structure used to manage the enaction of a scheme in the real world or the simulation of the enaction of a scheme in spatial memory.

setFinalContext

public void setFinalContext(IAct enactedAct,
                            IAct performedAct,
                            java.util.ArrayList<IAct> contextList)
Shift the context when a decision cycle terminates and the next begins. The context list is passed to the base context list. The activation list is reinitialized from the enacted act and the performed act. The context list is reinitialized from the activation list and the additional list provided as a parameter.

Specified by:
setFinalContext in interface IEnaction
Parameters:
enactedAct - The act that was actually enacted during the terminating decision cycle.
performedAct - The act that was performed during the terminating decision cycle.
contextList - The additional acts to add to the new context list
